WEBVTT

1
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:26.240
Ooh la la. Illumination!

2
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:30.040
<i>And now for a bedtime story.</i>

3
00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:36.520
<i>Once upon a time.</i>
<i>there was a beautiful pond.</i>

4
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:38.400
<i>It was paradise.</i>

5
00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:41.360
<i>Everyone was happy there.</i>

6
00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:45.280
<i>Well. not everyone.</i>

7
00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:49.280
<i>For two ducklings were suffering</i>
<i>from a strange condition.</i>

8
00:00:49.720 --> 00:00:51.000
<i>They were bored.</i>

9
00:00:53.040 --> 00:00:57.080
<i>And they were eager to discover what</i>
<i>lay beyond their cozy. little pond.</i>

10
00:00:57.160 --> 00:00:58.480
Come on. Let's have a look.

11
00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:01.200
But Daddy says
it's dangerous to leave the pond.

12
00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:04.440
We're brave and strong.
We ain't scared of nothing.

13
00:01:04.520 --> 00:01:07.240
<i>So they decided to go for it.</i>

14
00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:09.400
<i>Straight into the arms of...</i>

15
00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:11.200
<i>predators!</i>

16
00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.040
<i>They were surrounded. trapped.</i>

17
00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:21.840
<i>But the ducklings were not afraid.</i>

18
00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:25.000
<i>The tiny heroes attacked</i>
<i>the predator. and...</i>

19
00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:26.920
they died.

20
00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:28.240
The end.

21
00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:32.600
That's all? They're dead?

22
00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:34.360
Oh. yeah. No survivors.

23
00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:35.520
But how?

24
00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:37.000
Oh. you want details? Okay.

25
00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:38.920
So. first. the heron
cut them in half...

26
00:01:39.160 --> 00:01:41.600
Wait a second here.

27
00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:44.040
Your father got
the story wrong again.

28
00:01:44.120 --> 00:01:45.560
What really happened was

29
00:01:45.640 --> 00:01:49.320
<i>the heron saw that they were lost.</i>
<i>so she offered to help them.</i>

30
00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:50.760
<i>Pam. it's a heron.</i>

31
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:54.240
<i>A psycho killer</i>
<i>designed to eat ducklings.</i>

32
00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:56.920
<i>All right. fine.</i>
<i>The heron was about to eat them.</i>

33
00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.160
<i>But their parents arrived</i>
<i>just in time</i>

34
00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:01.560
- <i>and saved them.</i>
- <i>Oh</i>

35
00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:02.760
<i>no... nope.</i>

36
00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:05.640
<i>Their parents arrived.</i>
<i>but it was too late.</i>

37
00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:07.920
Oh. Dax. don't worry.

38
00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:09.320
It's going to be okay.

39
00:02:09.560 --> 00:02:10.760
Really. Dad?

40
00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:14.400
Yeah. sure. Squished ducks.
they can achieve great things. too.

41
00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:17.680
As long as they stay in the pond.
far from the dangers of the world

42
00:02:17.760 --> 00:02:22.000
such as herons and bears and wolves
and storms and cyclones

43
00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:25.480
and tornadoes and crocodiles
and poisonous mushrooms

44
00:02:25.560 --> 00:02:26.880
- Okay. I really need
- and flu. and

45
00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:27.960
- to get to bed now.
- duck flu

46
00:02:28.040 --> 00:02:29.040
and saber-toothed tigers...

47
00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:30.640
What happened to the other duckling?

48
00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:32.120
- and volcanoes...
- Was she squished. too?

49
00:02:32.200 --> 00:02:35.400
Oh. no. no. no. Don't worry. Gwen.
The ducklings were both safe.

50
00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:37.480
They just went on their way
right back to the pond.

51
00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:39.200
But another predator came in and...

52
00:02:39.280 --> 00:02:42.000
And wished them good day.

53
00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:43.440
The end.

54
00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:44.520
That's it.

55
00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:48.320
Okay.

56
00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:51.880
Good night. Mom. Good night. Dad.

57
00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:52.960
Good night.

58
00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:54.400
Good night. sweetie.

59
00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:57.760
- What?
- Every time you tell a story

60
00:02:57.840 --> 00:02:59.400
Gwen wets her twig bed.

61
00:02:59.480 --> 00:03:03.040
Does she? That's great. See?
That means she's learning. Pam.

62
00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:04.640
Oh. learning what?

63
00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:06.320
That she should never leave the pond?

64
00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:07.400
Exactly.

65
00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:09.840
Trust me. I'm teaching her
very valuable fears.

66
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:12.560
I should know. I've lived
with them my entire life.

67
00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:16.160
So have we all.

68
00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:18.080
Good night. honey.

69
00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:21.240
Good night. sweetheart.

70
00:03:44.080 --> 00:03:45.880
Ready. set. go!

71
00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:47.440
Come on. Gwenny! Come on!

72
00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:49.200
Let's go. Let's go.
Beat Daddy. Beat Daddy.

73
00:03:49.280 --> 00:03:51.920
Go... go! Oh. yay!

74
00:03:52.360 --> 00:03:53.360
I lost!

75
00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:56.040
Yes!

76
00:04:00.600 --> 00:04:01.600
Hey.

77
00:04:03.200 --> 00:04:04.280
Hello!

78
00:04:11.600 --> 00:04:12.600
No!

79
00:04:19.400 --> 00:04:20.400
Yay!

80
00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:21.480
- Mine!
- You're the worst!

81
00:04:21.560 --> 00:04:23.160
- That's mine!
- Got a thousand of 'em!

82
00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:25.560
Thanks. Dad!

83
00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:40.600
Okay. guys. Remember
to pick the fresh leaves.

84
00:04:40.680 --> 00:04:41.680
Okay. Dad.

85
00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:43.840
Is this one good. Dad?

86
00:04:44.040 --> 00:04:46.520
Perfect. Keep looking for more.

87
00:04:52.760 --> 00:04:54.880
Guys! Guys.
you have to see something.

88
00:04:54.960 --> 00:04:56.320
It's incredible. Come on. come on.

89
00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:57.680
Everybody. come. Come on.

90
00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:09.560
- Look! I told you!
- Yeah!

91
00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:12.000
- Isn't it beautiful?
- This is awesome!

92
00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:14.080
Have you ever seen ducks like that?

93
00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:26.720
Look at that.

94
00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:28.240
They must be migrating.

95
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:32.520
They seem so mysterious and exotic.

96
00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:34.200
I wonder where they flew in from.

97
00:05:34.280 --> 00:05:35.440
Maybe we should go say hi.

98
00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:38.440
- Should we?
- No. Oh. look at these feathers.

99
00:05:38.520 --> 00:05:39.520
No. I wanna know.

100
00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:41.640
Let's go ask 'em. Mack. come on.

101
00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:43.560
Yeah. no. I'm good.

102
00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:46.600
Come on. We never meet anyone new.

103
00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:48.160
Okay. fine.

104
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:51.880
All right. kids. let's go
meet Mom's new friends.

105
00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:53.800
Kids?

106
00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:56.240
Kids? Kids?

107
00:05:56.920 --> 00:05:58.160
Pretty good progress. huh?

108
00:05:58.240 --> 00:06:00.200
- Yeah. Got to love a tailwind.
- Yeah.

109
00:06:00.280 --> 00:06:01.840
- Hello.
- Hello.

110
00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:03.000
Welcome to the pond.

111
00:06:03.080 --> 00:06:04.120
- Thank you.
- Hey there.

112
00:06:04.200 --> 00:06:05.400
- Oh. hi.
- Nice feathers.

113
00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:06.640
We shouldn't be here. Dax.

114
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:08.040
Dad is gonna be mad.

115
00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:09.440
Go back to the parents. Gwen.

116
00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:10.800
- Hey there.
- Dax!

117
00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.080
- Come on!
- What are you doing?

118
00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:13.480
I don't wanna be psycho-killed!

119
00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:16.000
Let me go. you little feathery wart!

120
00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:18.640
Okay. I'm a feathery wart?

121
00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:19.760
You don't even know me.

122
00:06:19.840 --> 00:06:22.160
No... no. She's a feathery wart.

123
00:06:22.240 --> 00:06:24.600
You're a very nice wart.
I mean wart duck.

124
00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:26.000
- I mean...
- I'm kidding.

125
00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:27.600
Oh. Right.

126
00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:31.400
Hi. I'm Kim.

127
00:06:31.480 --> 00:06:33.000
Hi. I'm Dax.

128
00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:34.400
Welcome to Moosehead Pond.

129
00:06:34.480 --> 00:06:35.920
Welcome to na-na-na.

130
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.040
You and your flock can stay here
as long as you like.

131
00:06:38.120 --> 00:06:39.400
I could show you around.

132
00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:42.120
I mean. this is
pretty much it. but...

133
00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:46.320
Thanks. But we're just passing by
on our way down south.

134
00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:48.240
We're gonna spend the winter there.
Where are you guys going?

135
00:06:48.320 --> 00:06:50.760
We spend winter here
to avoid psycho killers like your...

136
00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:52.760
Sorry. Wart.

137
00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:55.840
Wait. So you don't go anywhere
for the winter?

138
00:06:56.520 --> 00:06:57.520
Nope.

139
00:06:58.200 --> 00:06:59.760
You should totally come with us.

140
00:06:59.840 --> 00:07:01.240
What? Really?

141
00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:03.280
Yes! Your flock could
totally join ours.

142
00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:05.080
Oh. my gosh. this will be so cool.

143
00:07:05.160 --> 00:07:07.680
You will love migrating.
The sun. the sand.

144
00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:10.200
Wait. Do you like tropical food?
What's your take on bananas?

145
00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:12.320
- I don't...
- You're gonna love 'em!

146
00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:13.880
You hold this. I'll go ask my dad.

147
00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:15.160
Dad! Dad!

148
00:07:15.240 --> 00:07:17.080
- What just happened?
- Dad!

149
00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:19.000
I don't know. but you're in trouble.

150
00:07:19.320 --> 00:07:20.760
Dax! Gwen!

151
00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:23.360
Are you crazy? You can't
just take off like that.

152
00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.360
- He made me do it!
- What?

153
00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:27.400
And he talked to a girl.

154
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:28.720
- A girl?
- Gwen!

155
00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.560
Yeah. and he told her
he wants to marry her.

156
00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:33.560
What? I didn't say that!

157
00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:35.560
You said it with your eyes.

158
00:07:35.680 --> 00:07:36.680
Dad. he's hitting me!

159
00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:38.200
- He's hitting me!
- Hey... hey! Enough! Enough!

160
00:07:38.280 --> 00:07:40.160
- Sibling cruelty!
- Enough.

161
00:07:41.240 --> 00:07:43.760
Okay. Hello. Hi. Hi. Big hellos.

162
00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:45.000
And we're good. Let's go.

163
00:07:45.080 --> 00:07:46.480
- Mack.
- What? I said hi.

164
00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.040
I smiled. I made eye contact.

165
00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:49.400
I checked all the boxes.

166
00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:50.480
Hey there.

167
00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:52.640
I hear you wanna join our migration.

168
00:07:53.560 --> 00:07:54.560
Sorry?

169
00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:57.560
Oh. we're going back to Jamaica.
Have you ever been?

170
00:07:58.040 --> 00:07:59.040
No.

171
00:07:59.120 --> 00:08:01.120
Oh. it's just magical.

172
00:08:01.200 --> 00:08:02.960
I swear. there's even
a luminous lagoon

173
00:08:03.040 --> 00:08:04.320
where the water glows.

174
00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:06.840
Oh. wow. Oh. I really wanna see that.

175
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:08.760
Well. then it is settled.

176
00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:11.720
Your whole flock can join us.
This is gonna be great.

177
00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:12.920
Oh. gosh. That's...

178
00:08:13.400 --> 00:08:14.640
That's just so nice of you.

179
00:08:14.720 --> 00:08:15.760
Wait. wait. wait.

180
00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:18.760
I think there's a slight
misunderstanding here.

181
00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:22.000
Unfortunately. we're just slammed
this winter. Aren't we. Pam?

182
00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:24.280
'Cause we've got the thing.
and then the...

183
00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:25.640
We've got the thing after that.

184
00:08:25.720 --> 00:08:27.600
So. you know what? We can't go.

185
00:08:27.680 --> 00:08:28.920
But you guys go.

186
00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.120
Have a great time.

187
00:08:30.200 --> 00:08:32.920
And. you know.
tell the glowing water we said hi.

188
00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:36.880
Well. maybe next year. then?

189
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:38.920
You got it. Next year!

190
00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:43.480
Well. guess it's time for us to go.

191
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:49.120
Have a nice trip.

192
00:08:50.560 --> 00:08:51.560
Thanks.

193
00:08:51.960 --> 00:08:54.320
Have a nice... pond.

194
00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:05.360
I'm so sorry you can't
have babies with her.

195
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:14.120
That was so... rude!

196
00:09:14.200 --> 00:09:15.200
I know.

197
00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:16.800
"Have a nice pond."

198
00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:17.920
Who says that?

199
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:19.480
That's just poor parenting.

200
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:21.200
Not them. You!

201
00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:22.280
Me?

202
00:09:22.360 --> 00:09:23.800
Yes. you.

203
00:09:24.040 --> 00:09:26.680
Okay. So I got a little carried away.

204
00:09:26.760 --> 00:09:27.800
But migration?

205
00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:29.600
What a stupid idea.

206
00:09:30.120 --> 00:09:32.080
- Okay. You're impossible.
- Why?

207
00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:35.760
Because I found a safe place
for us to live and we're happy here?

208
00:09:35.840 --> 00:09:37.520
You mean you're happy here.

209
00:09:38.400 --> 00:09:40.200
- What?
- I want us to get out

210
00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:41.280
and see the world.

211
00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:42.840
- Me. too. Dad.
- Yeah.

212
00:09:42.920 --> 00:09:45.680
I want to go to Jamai... Jam... J...

213
00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:47.040
where they make jam.

214
00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:49.320
You... you really want those things?

215
00:09:49.520 --> 00:09:50.600
- Yes.
- Yes.

216
00:09:50.680 --> 00:09:52.760
- Really?
- Yes.

217
00:09:52.840 --> 00:09:54.200
No home improvements?

218
00:09:54.400 --> 00:09:56.680
- No!
- Yes. I mean... I mean no.

219
00:09:57.840 --> 00:09:59.880
Do you know what can happen
on a trip that long?

220
00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:02.800
What sort of father would I be
if I put my young fowl in harm's way

221
00:10:02.880 --> 00:10:05.800
for no reason except
a chance at a Caribbean vacation?

222
00:10:05.880 --> 00:10:07.920
A father who knows
it's important for his kids

223
00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.600
to see other parts of the world.

224
00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:11.280
Mack. I don't wanna miss out on life

225
00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:13.120
because you're afraid
to leave this pond.

226
00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:15.600
This isn't about migration.

227
00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:19.000
It's about adventure.

228
00:10:19.080 --> 00:10:21.720
Seeing what else life has to offer.

229
00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:23.560
Is that a little scary? Sure.

230
00:10:24.320 --> 00:10:25.760
But isn't it worth it?

231
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:28.640
No. Pam.

232
00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:30.200
Not really.

233
00:10:34.360 --> 00:10:36.880
You really need
to open your eyes. Mack

234
00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:39.880
before you miss it all.

235
00:10:40.920 --> 00:10:41.920
Come on. kids.

236
00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:02.600
Uncle Dan. what are you doing here?

237
00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:05.960
I don't know.

238
00:11:06.040 --> 00:11:08.120
I must have drifted
from my nest again.

239
00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:12.760
Be a good boy and get me back there.

240
00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:14.080
Give me a little push.

241
00:11:14.920 --> 00:11:15.920
All right.

242
00:11:23.440 --> 00:11:24.440
Thank you.

243
00:11:25.600 --> 00:11:27.760
I heard the little family tiff.

244
00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:29.360
I gotta say...

245
00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:31.160
you're right.

246
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:32.760
Wha... I am?

247
00:11:33.200 --> 00:11:34.200
Please.

248
00:11:34.280 --> 00:11:35.480
What's all the travel talk?

249
00:11:35.560 --> 00:11:39.520
I mean. why can't we be satisfied
with what we already have?

250
00:11:39.600 --> 00:11:40.880
Well. yeah.

251
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:45.000
I mean. you got food right here.
We got a pond right here. Right?

252
00:11:45.080 --> 00:11:47.080
Yeah. Food. the pond.

253
00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:48.680
Why go anywhere else?

254
00:11:48.760 --> 00:11:50.400
Stick to your beliefs. kid.

255
00:11:50.480 --> 00:11:51.920
Don't change for anyone.

256
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.600
- Exactly.
- And you'll end up just like me.

257
00:11:54.680 --> 00:11:56.240
- Happy.
- Yeah.

258
00:11:56.320 --> 00:11:57.360
- Healthy.
- Yeah.

259
00:11:57.440 --> 00:11:58.920
And totally alone!

260
00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:00.840
Yeah! Wait. what?

261
00:12:00.920 --> 00:12:02.000
That's right.

262
00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:04.960
You'll be living the dream.

263
00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:08.320
That was exhausting.

264
00:12:08.400 --> 00:12:09.920
I'm gonna just rest here.

265
00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:16.720
Rise and shine. Mallards!

266
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:19.280
We're burning daylight.
Up and at 'em.

267
00:12:19.360 --> 00:12:20.760
Let's go. go. go!

268
00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:22.400
Here's breakfast.

269
00:12:23.280 --> 00:12:24.600
Dad. what are you doing?

270
00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:26.200
Getting your sorry feathers
out of bed.

271
00:12:26.280 --> 00:12:28.080
Come on. We gotta get ready.

272
00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:30.400
Mack. ready for what?

273
00:12:30.480 --> 00:12:36.520
Nothing. Just. you know. for
our big. super fun family migration!

274
00:12:36.600 --> 00:12:37.600
What?

275
00:12:38.200 --> 00:12:39.640
Bet you didn't see that coming.

276
00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:40.880
Are you serious?

277
00:12:40.960 --> 00:12:44.000
Yep. An adventure
into the totally unknown.

278
00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:46.080
And I'm gonna love it.

279
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:48.280
Is this real?

280
00:12:48.360 --> 00:12:49.880
What do you mean. "Is this real?"

281
00:12:49.960 --> 00:12:50.960
We're really going?

282
00:12:51.040 --> 00:12:52.080
- Yes.
- On a migration?

283
00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:53.520
To Jamaica?

284
00:12:53.600 --> 00:12:54.760
- Yeah.
- Together?

285
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:55.840
- Yes.
- Like. everyone?

286
00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:58.280
- Yes.
- Including you?

287
00:12:58.360 --> 00:13:00.480
Yes! We are all going on
a migration to Jamaica.

288
00:13:00.560 --> 00:13:02.040
In which language should I tell you?

289
00:13:02.280 --> 00:13:03.280
Thanks. Dad.

290
00:13:04.600 --> 00:13:05.680
You're welcome.

291
00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:09.720
I knew there was
some adventure left in you.

292
00:13:10.880 --> 00:13:12.360
Wait. wait. wait!

293
00:13:19.520 --> 00:13:21.560
- Uncle Dan. you're coming. too!
- Gwen

294
00:13:21.640 --> 00:13:23.760
- No... no.
- We're going to Jamaica.

295
00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:25.920
No. I don't think so. kiddo.

296
00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:28.920
- Oh. please. Uncle Dan.
- Nah.

297
00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:30.520
Oh. too bad he doesn't
wanna come. honey.

298
00:13:30.600 --> 00:13:32.400
We tried. What else
can we do? Let's leave.

299
00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:42.600
Please...

300
00:13:47.880 --> 00:13:48.960
Pretty please?

301
00:13:49.880 --> 00:13:51.640
That did it. I can't refuse her.

302
00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.760
Look at her. Look at how cute she is.

303
00:13:53.840 --> 00:13:56.000
Yes! Uncle Dan is coming!

304
00:13:56.080 --> 00:13:57.800
- No. he's not.
- Uncle Dan. Uncle Dan.

305
00:13:57.880 --> 00:13:59.280
- Uncle Dan. Uncle Dan.
- Uncle Dan. Uncle Dan.

306
00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:00.880
- Oh. for real?
- Uncle Dan. Uncle Dan.

307
00:14:00.960 --> 00:14:02.400
Uncle Dan. Uncle Dan.

308
00:14:02.480 --> 00:14:04.400
- That's me.
- Uncle Dan. Yeah!

309
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.640
Yay.

310
00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:15.040
Here we go. Let's do the final check.

311
00:14:15.440 --> 00:14:16.880
Tail feather torsion?

312
00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:18.600
Check.

313
00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:21.120
- Wing deployment?
- Check.

314
00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:23.240
Heads in takeoff mode?

315
00:14:24.040 --> 00:14:25.040
Check.

316
00:14:26.120 --> 00:14:27.360
Let's fly.

317
00:14:46.680 --> 00:14:47.680
Yeah!

318
00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:54.920
Yeah!

319
00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:03.200
Okay. everyone.
enough fooling around.

320
00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:05.440
V-formation.

321
00:15:06.560 --> 00:15:08.880
- Yeah! Look at me!
- Thanks. Dad!

322
00:15:09.520 --> 00:15:11.120
Yeah. this is awesome!

323
00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:13.200
Well. better get used to it.

324
00:15:24.040 --> 00:15:26.240
That's weird. My inner compass
may be a little rusty

325
00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:28.400
but I'm sure we're heading south.

326
00:15:28.720 --> 00:15:32.400
Yeah. we are. but why are we
the only birds heading this way?

327
00:15:40.600 --> 00:15:42.120
Hey. kids. don't worry.

328
00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:43.520
We're gonna be all right.

329
00:15:43.600 --> 00:15:45.080
Here we are together.

330
00:15:45.160 --> 00:15:46.680
We're on an adventure.

331
00:15:46.760 --> 00:15:50.920
I promised adventure. and
this is exactly what I promised. huh?

332
00:15:52.960 --> 00:15:54.120
We're not gonna make it. are we?

333
00:15:54.200 --> 00:15:56.520
- Uncle Dan!
- You can tell me. I don't mind.

334
00:15:56.600 --> 00:15:58.440
I'm a big boy. I'm a big duck.

335
00:15:58.520 --> 00:16:00.760
No. Uncle Dan.
things are gonna be fine.

336
00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:02.040
Isn't that right. Mack?

337
00:16:03.120 --> 00:16:04.120
I...

338
00:16:05.040 --> 00:16:07.720
I mean yes. Mom's right.

339
00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:09.440
This is fun.

340
00:16:09.520 --> 00:16:12.240
This is the kinda thing
we'll remember for years to come.

341
00:16:12.360 --> 00:16:14.360
We'll look back and laugh.

342
00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:34.920
- A heron.
- The one from Dad's story.

343
00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:36.680
The ultimate duck killer.

344
00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:40.000
Don't panic. Herons can't see
their prey if you stay still.

345
00:16:42.080 --> 00:16:44.800
Hello. little ducks.

346
00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:46.880
She's bluffing.

347
00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:48.880
So. tell me

348
00:16:48.960 --> 00:16:53.040
what's a nice little family
of mallards doing down here

349
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.000
all cold and wet?

350
00:16:55.280 --> 00:16:57.000
Nothing. We're good.

351
00:16:57.880 --> 00:16:58.880
We're enjoying it.

352
00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:01.240
But you must be freezing here.

353
00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:02.600
- Oh. no. we're not.
- Come.

354
00:17:02.680 --> 00:17:03.720
- Oh. no... no.
- Come. come.

355
00:17:03.920 --> 00:17:08.200
Let Erin take care of you
in her comfy little nest.

356
00:17:11.480 --> 00:17:13.360
In you go. Hup. hup. hup.

357
00:17:13.440 --> 00:17:14.840
Harry!

358
00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:16.680
Harry. look.

359
00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:18.000
Look what I found.

360
00:17:18.360 --> 00:17:22.520
A nice little family
of traveling mallards.

361
00:17:22.840 --> 00:17:25.000
Mallards.

362
00:17:29.840 --> 00:17:31.640
Okay. Nice meeting you all.

363
00:17:31.840 --> 00:17:32.840
Bye-bye.

364
00:17:32.920 --> 00:17:35.000
In a rush. are you?

365
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:40.200
Oh. we don't wanna be a bother.
You look busy decaying.

366
00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:42.320
You're not bothering at all.

367
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:48.120
But maybe herons are not
good enough for you

368
00:17:48.600 --> 00:17:49.880
mallards?

369
00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:53.400
No. of course not.
We're happy to stay.

370
00:17:56.880 --> 00:17:59.320
Good! Let me get your bed ready.

371
00:17:59.680 --> 00:18:01.720
What do they do.
rip you apart. then eat you?

372
00:18:01.800 --> 00:18:03.360
- Dan.
- I don't know how they do it.

373
00:18:03.440 --> 00:18:05.320
- What's the method?
- Hey. Zip it.

374
00:18:06.200 --> 00:18:08.000
Wake me up
when it's my turn to be eaten.

375
00:18:08.080 --> 00:18:09.680
- What?
- What are you doing. Pam?

376
00:18:09.760 --> 00:18:12.080
Well. I don't know. I just...
I don't want to offend them.

377
00:18:12.160 --> 00:18:13.560
Can't you see they want to eat us?

378
00:18:13.640 --> 00:18:14.760
I don't wanna be eaten!

379
00:18:14.840 --> 00:18:15.880
Well. she can't eat us.

380
00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:17.000
She doesn't have teeth.

381
00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:18.840
Well. what if she cuts us
into pieces first?

382
00:18:18.920 --> 00:18:20.480
I don't wanna be cut into piece...

383
00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:22.360
I beg your pardon?

384
00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:26.560
Oh. what's that? No. no. We were just
saying your nest is just so charming.

385
00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:27.640
Weren't we. kids?

386
00:18:28.280 --> 00:18:30.240
Oh. thank you.

387
00:18:30.320 --> 00:18:32.360
We moved here a few years ago.

388
00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:35.120
We used to migrate
all the time like you.

389
00:18:35.360 --> 00:18:38.040
Harry was such an adventurer

390
00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:39.680
and a fierce predator. too.

391
00:18:39.760 --> 00:18:43.800
He could catch any prey
with a single swift peck.

392
00:18:51.800 --> 00:18:54.760
Those were the good old days.

393
00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:57.760
Now Harry's too old.

394
00:18:57.960 --> 00:19:03.400
I'm the one who brings food
back to the nest.

395
00:19:05.720 --> 00:19:08.800
But. anyway. you must be exhausted.

396
00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:10.000
Here's your bed.

397
00:19:11.240 --> 00:19:12.880
There's no way
we're sleeping in that.

398
00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:15.280
But it's our finest bed.

399
00:19:15.360 --> 00:19:17.880
And it is perfect. Thank you.

400
00:19:19.040 --> 00:19:20.040
Wow. huh?

401
00:19:20.120 --> 00:19:23.280
Hey. feel this.
Even comfier than our own nest.

402
00:19:23.360 --> 00:19:24.680
Yeah. sure.

403
00:19:25.040 --> 00:19:26.760
It's greasier. too.

404
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:31.160
Looks like
your last guest is still here.

405
00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:32.640
And dead.

406
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:34.400
Thank you.

407
00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:37.000
You're welcome. sweethearts.

408
00:19:37.480 --> 00:19:38.880
Sleep tight.

409
00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:41.560
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

410
00:19:54.760 --> 00:19:57.920
Okay. Storm is over.
Let's go. Kids. kids. wake up.

411
00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.520
- Pam. we gotta go right now.
- What?

412
00:19:59.600 --> 00:20:01.080
- Right now!
- Now?

413
00:20:01.160 --> 00:20:02.800
- What about Uncle Dan?
- It's fine.

414
00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:03.920
When they wake up.
they'll eat him.

415
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:05.360
That'll give us more time to lose...

416
00:20:07.320 --> 00:20:08.760
You're awake.

417
00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:10.760
Looking right at us. too.

418
00:20:10.840 --> 00:20:11.880
Bonus.

419
00:20:12.840 --> 00:20:16.480
You shouldn't have
gotten out of your beds.

420
00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:21.320
Nighttime is when
predators like to feed.

421
00:20:21.400 --> 00:20:22.600
Stay away from my kids.

422
00:20:22.680 --> 00:20:24.800
Let's do this quick!

423
00:20:26.160 --> 00:20:27.320
Run. kids. run!

424
00:20:27.400 --> 00:20:28.520
Let me get them!

425
00:20:30.280 --> 00:20:32.120
Harry. catch them!

426
00:20:34.320 --> 00:20:35.560
Head for the door!

427
00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:42.600
Go. go!

428
00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:47.320
Hands off!

429
00:20:48.800 --> 00:20:50.520
It's okay. kids.

430
00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:52.200
Just hold still.

431
00:20:52.280 --> 00:20:53.400
No... no.

432
00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:56.960
Please don't eat us.
We haven't finished molting yet.

433
00:20:57.040 --> 00:20:58.320
Pretty please?

434
00:20:58.400 --> 00:21:01.040
I promise you this won't hurt.

435
00:21:06.960 --> 00:21:07.960
No!

436
00:21:10.600 --> 00:21:11.600
Gotcha!

437
00:21:11.680 --> 00:21:14.960
He was about to gulp you in one bite.

438
00:21:15.040 --> 00:21:16.160
Bad fish.

439
00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:18.560
Ooh. bad fish!

440
00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:22.480
You... you saved them?

441
00:21:22.560 --> 00:21:23.560
Oh.

442
00:21:24.320 --> 00:21:25.640
It was nothing.

443
00:21:25.720 --> 00:21:28.280
And we have breakfast for tomorrow.

444
00:21:28.360 --> 00:21:29.760
Right. Harry?

445
00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:34.000
Into beddy-byes now.

446
00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:57.320
Are you sure you have to go already?
I'll miss your kids so much.

447
00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:59.760
They are so adorable.

448
00:22:02.240 --> 00:22:05.040
And you taste so good.

449
00:22:05.480 --> 00:22:07.440
Maybe I'll eat you.

450
00:22:08.080 --> 00:22:09.520
I'm kidding.

451
00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:13.240
Or am I?

452
00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:17.880
- It's a joke! It's a joke.
- Oh.

453
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:20.400
So funny.

454
00:22:21.080 --> 00:22:24.200
All right. Time to go.
Thanks for everything.

455
00:22:25.400 --> 00:22:26.400
Goodbye.

456
00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:28.000
I haven't kissed Harry goodbye!

457
00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:30.040
No... no. Blow him a kiss.

458
00:22:31.840 --> 00:22:33.320
No... no. you don't
have to walk closer.

459
00:22:33.400 --> 00:22:35.640
You're good there. Bye. Harry.
Thanks so much.

460
00:22:36.280 --> 00:22:39.560
Don't forget.
drop by on your way back.

461
00:22:42.560 --> 00:22:43.800
Wild night there. huh?

462
00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:45.920
Yeah.

463
00:22:46.200 --> 00:22:47.200
Yeah.

464
00:22:47.880 --> 00:22:49.200
How about when she pulled out
that pan. though?

465
00:22:49.280 --> 00:22:52.320
Oh. my gosh! With the dead fish
still in the pan?

466
00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:53.720
- The dead fish.
- Terrifying.

467
00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:55.800
Right? Still. lovely birds.

468
00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.840
Oh. lovely.

469
00:22:57.920 --> 00:22:59.200
Lovely birds.

470
00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:02.480
Guys! Come up!

471
00:23:03.120 --> 00:23:04.920
You have to see this.

472
00:23:06.040 --> 00:23:09.480
Hey. hey. hey. Dax. let's keep
the adventure where I can see you.

473
00:23:25.960 --> 00:23:27.120
- Yeah!
- Come on!

474
00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:28.200
Try it. Dad!

475
00:23:28.280 --> 00:23:31.600
Okay. okay. this is pretty cool.
but we should probably get back on...

476
00:23:33.240 --> 00:23:35.280
Don't be such a stick-in-the-mud!

477
00:23:51.600 --> 00:23:52.600
Yeah!

478
00:23:54.720 --> 00:23:55.840
Hello!

479
00:23:58.440 --> 00:24:00.240
- Peekaboo!
- Whoa! Dad!

480
00:24:09.960 --> 00:24:11.360
Ow. Hey. watch out.

481
00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:12.720
Hey!

482
00:24:17.240 --> 00:24:18.400
Gotcha!

483
00:24:19.840 --> 00:24:21.120
That was fun.

484
00:24:21.200 --> 00:24:22.800
Let's go down before we lose our way.

485
00:24:22.880 --> 00:24:24.400
Please. Dad. come on.

486
00:24:24.520 --> 00:24:25.880
- Just a bit more.
- Please. Dad?

487
00:24:25.960 --> 00:24:28.560
Okay. okay. just a little bit longer.

488
00:24:29.240 --> 00:24:30.800
What is that?

489
00:25:58.760 --> 00:26:00.320
Guys. you okay?

490
00:26:00.960 --> 00:26:02.800
Yeah! What a ride.

491
00:26:02.960 --> 00:26:04.120
Let's do it again.

492
00:26:04.600 --> 00:26:05.600
Yeah!

493
00:26:06.160 --> 00:26:07.240
Your mother.

494
00:26:07.320 --> 00:26:08.320
Where's your mother?

495
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.000
Pam?

496
00:26:12.720 --> 00:26:14.000
That is not your mother.

497
00:26:14.080 --> 00:26:15.080
Up here!

498
00:26:15.680 --> 00:26:18.200
Fly up. We can see
so much better from up here.

499
00:26:18.280 --> 00:26:19.480
Pam! Are you hurt somewhere?

500
00:26:19.560 --> 00:26:21.280
- Do you feel pain? What's your name?
- What? I'm fine.

501
00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:22.600
How many feathers am I holding up?

502
00:26:22.680 --> 00:26:24.440
Hey. I'm fine.

503
00:26:27.280 --> 00:26:28.400
Thank goodness.

504
00:26:28.880 --> 00:26:30.000
Okay.

505
00:26:30.080 --> 00:26:33.000
Come on. everyone. Prepare
for takeoff so we can get out of...

506
00:26:35.040 --> 00:26:36.200
here.

507
00:26:37.240 --> 00:26:38.880
What is this place?

508
00:26:38.960 --> 00:26:40.480
I... I don't know.

509
00:26:40.840 --> 00:26:42.280
We've never been this far before.

510
00:26:42.360 --> 00:26:44.760
Uncle Dan. have you
ever been here before?

511
00:26:45.640 --> 00:26:46.640
Uncle Dan?

512
00:26:47.680 --> 00:26:49.840
Hello? Guys?

513
00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:51.360
Anyone?

514
00:26:51.720 --> 00:26:53.000
I don't like heights.

515
00:27:06.840 --> 00:27:08.680
- Uncle Dan?
- Yeah. it's me!

516
00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:09.960
It's Uncle Dan!

517
00:27:10.040 --> 00:27:11.040
Uncle Dan!

518
00:27:14.080 --> 00:27:16.080
Well. he led a good life.

519
00:27:17.040 --> 00:27:19.680
- What?
- We're coming for you. Uncle Dan!

520
00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:21.720
He would have wanted us
to go on without him.

521
00:27:22.080 --> 00:27:24.760
Come on. he was kind like that.

522
00:27:43.360 --> 00:27:45.120
Well. hello there.

523
00:27:57.120 --> 00:27:58.120
Get away. get away!

524
00:28:00.360 --> 00:28:01.360
Pigeons.

525
00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:10.560
Uncle Dan!

526
00:28:11.440 --> 00:28:13.360
- Uncle Dan!
- Uncle Dan!

527
00:28:13.440 --> 00:28:14.520
Uncle Dan. where are you?

528
00:28:14.600 --> 00:28:15.840
- Uncle Dan!
- Uncle Dan?

529
00:28:15.920 --> 00:28:17.520
What if something ate Uncle Dan?

530
00:28:17.600 --> 00:28:20.520
Honey. I promise you. nothing
would ever wanna eat Uncle Dan.

531
00:28:21.720 --> 00:28:22.720
Uncle Dan.

532
00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:24.520
Get off me!

533
00:28:25.040 --> 00:28:26.920
I'm coming!

534
00:28:28.240 --> 00:28:29.680
Hey. wait! Wait!

535
00:28:30.240 --> 00:28:31.360
Get away from me! Get away from me!

536
00:28:31.440 --> 00:28:32.800
It's my sandwich.

537
00:28:33.600 --> 00:28:36.400
I licked it. I licked it! You can't
touch it with duck spit on it.

538
00:28:36.480 --> 00:28:38.920
- Uncle Dan!
- Get your wings off my uncle!

539
00:28:40.480 --> 00:28:41.920
Dax. Gwen. wait!

540
00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:43.200
Stay away from my family!

541
00:28:43.280 --> 00:28:44.920
Back away! Back away! Back away!

542
00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:48.960
Get out of here.
you trashy. trashy vermin!

543
00:28:51.640 --> 00:28:53.320
Who said that?

544
00:28:55.680 --> 00:29:00.600
I asked. "Who said that?"

545
00:29:16.120 --> 00:29:17.560
Come here. bumpkin.

546
00:29:25.280 --> 00:29:26.400
Say it again.

547
00:29:27.560 --> 00:29:32.240
- Which part?
- "Trashy. trashy vermin."

548
00:29:32.520 --> 00:29:35.400
Let the record reflect.
I just meant to say "trashy vermin."

549
00:29:36.240 --> 00:29:37.880
Which I'm not saying that's good

550
00:29:38.160 --> 00:29:41.400
but I wasn't doubling down
on "trashy." vermin.

551
00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:45.800
You ducks make me sick.
you know that?

552
00:29:46.480 --> 00:29:49.760
You're fed all day
by the humans in the park

553
00:29:49.840 --> 00:29:51.080
but that's not enough for you.

554
00:29:51.160 --> 00:29:52.560
No. no. no.

555
00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:54.680
You gotta come to our territory.

556
00:29:54.800 --> 00:29:56.720
You gotta steal our food.

557
00:29:56.800 --> 00:29:59.080
And then you insult us?

558
00:29:59.240 --> 00:30:00.560
What? No... no. I wasn't...

559
00:30:00.640 --> 00:30:01.800
- Name!
- Mack.

560
00:30:03.480 --> 00:30:05.320
Well. "Uh. Mack."

561
00:30:05.920 --> 00:30:07.240
I'm the Chump

562
00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:10.480
and I'm the leader
of this group of hardworking birds

563
00:30:10.560 --> 00:30:12.040
you just called vermin.

564
00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:17.720
Okay... okay. So listen. Chump...

565
00:30:17.800 --> 00:30:19.240
What did you just call me?

566
00:30:19.320 --> 00:30:21.400
Sorry. I thought
your name was Chump.

567
00:30:21.520 --> 00:30:22.680
Yeah. Chump. yeah.
That's my name. Why?

568
00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:24.000
Right. So listen. Chump...

569
00:30:24.080 --> 00:30:25.160
What did you just call me?

570
00:30:25.240 --> 00:30:28.000
I'm sorry. Is everyone else
hearing "Chump" or...

571
00:30:28.080 --> 00:30:29.680
- What did... What?
- Okay. okay.

572
00:30:29.760 --> 00:30:32.400
I think there's a slight
misunderstanding here.

573
00:30:32.480 --> 00:30:35.080
Excuse me. Will you excuse me?
Coming through. Thank you.

574
00:30:35.160 --> 00:30:37.080
Okay. Hi there. I'm Pam.

575
00:30:37.160 --> 00:30:39.080
I'm sharing my life with him.
so I'm painfully aware

576
00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:41.480
of all the stupid things
that come out of his mouth.

577
00:30:42.520 --> 00:30:43.960
Oh. yeah. that's true. She is.

578
00:30:44.040 --> 00:30:46.840
But I assure you. he meant no harm.

579
00:30:46.920 --> 00:30:49.520
And to show our gratitude
for your understanding in this matter

580
00:30:49.800 --> 00:30:51.960
how about we share the sandwich?

581
00:30:52.040 --> 00:30:53.200
50-50.

582
00:30:57.520 --> 00:30:58.880
80-20.

583
00:30:58.960 --> 00:30:59.960
60-40.

584
00:31:00.040 --> 00:31:01.680
- 70-30.
- 65-35.

585
00:31:01.760 --> 00:31:02.760
68-32!

586
00:31:02.840 --> 00:31:04.120
67-33!

587
00:31:05.520 --> 00:31:06.880
You got yourself a deal.

588
00:31:06.960 --> 00:31:08.680
Uncle Dan. cut the sandwich.

589
00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:13.840
You don't wanna try 50-50 again?

590
00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:14.920
Uncle Dan!

591
00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:16.160
All right. all right.

592
00:31:20.360 --> 00:31:21.840
You. I like.

593
00:31:22.160 --> 00:31:23.160
Thank you. Chump.

594
00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:25.720
Sorry for busting your bills
over here. but...

595
00:31:26.880 --> 00:31:28.800
sometimes I get sensitive. is all.

596
00:31:28.880 --> 00:31:30.920
Us pigeons. we got big hearts. too.

597
00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:32.040
Ain't that right. guys?

598
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:33.800
Oh. for sure.

599
00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:35.080
We just want to be loved.

600
00:31:35.160 --> 00:31:36.680
And respected.

601
00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:42.840
Yeah. So anything you need.
I mean anything

602
00:31:42.920 --> 00:31:43.920
Chump's got ya.

603
00:31:44.000 --> 00:31:46.680
Oh. really? Because
we are completely lost.

604
00:31:46.760 --> 00:31:48.000
We're trying to get to Jamaica.

605
00:31:48.080 --> 00:31:49.600
Oh. yeah. yeah.
That's in Queens. right?

606
00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:52.520
More south. Like. the Caribbean.

607
00:31:52.680 --> 00:31:54.840
Oh. that Jamaica.

608
00:31:54.920 --> 00:31:57.640
I got a buddy who knows that place
like the back of his wing.

609
00:31:57.720 --> 00:31:59.240
You... you think he'll help us?

610
00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:02.720
Yeah. I mean. it's a bit
of a sore subject for him

611
00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:05.040
but I'm sure it won't be a problem.

612
00:32:05.120 --> 00:32:07.280
Come on. lovebirds.
we ain't got all day.

613
00:32:07.360 --> 00:32:08.440
It's this way.

614
00:32:08.720 --> 00:32:11.480
Wow. Mom. you rock.

615
00:32:11.560 --> 00:32:13.400
Yeah. 60-40!

616
00:32:14.040 --> 00:32:16.840
- 70-30!
- 60.000-3.500!

617
00:32:16.920 --> 00:32:18.560
I didn't know you could be so tough.

618
00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:21.000
Really. Mack? You didn't know that?

619
00:32:21.080 --> 00:32:22.240
Oh. no. I...

620
00:32:23.840 --> 00:32:24.880
Oh!

621
00:32:25.320 --> 00:32:26.520
I get it.

622
00:32:26.600 --> 00:32:27.760
That's good.

623
00:32:28.120 --> 00:32:29.200
That's very good.

624
00:32:32.080 --> 00:32:34.760
Okay. my little bumpkins.
let's get a move on.

625
00:32:34.840 --> 00:32:35.880
Are you kidding?

626
00:32:35.960 --> 00:32:38.880
We are not flying through this
crazy death trap of a city again.

627
00:32:38.960 --> 00:32:41.000
Oh. come on. It's nothing.

628
00:32:41.080 --> 00:32:45.240
Just stick close to me.
and everything will be all right.

629
00:32:51.280 --> 00:32:53.600
I'm okay. Yeah. no. I'm okay!

630
00:32:54.800 --> 00:32:55.800
Yeah.

631
00:32:58.480 --> 00:32:59.480
I'm okay.

632
00:32:59.760 --> 00:33:00.800
I'm still okay.

633
00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:02.240
We can do this.

634
00:33:04.760 --> 00:33:06.120
You missed. bus!

635
00:33:10.560 --> 00:33:12.000
Maybe don't stick too close.

636
00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:36.520
Here you go. my little princess.

637
00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:38.200
Thank you!

638
00:33:39.840 --> 00:33:42.480
Gwen! I got you. Gwen. I got you.

639
00:33:44.320 --> 00:33:46.000
Look! Look. there it is.

640
00:33:46.440 --> 00:33:47.760
That's Jamaica.

641
00:33:51.640 --> 00:33:52.640
What?

642
00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:11.160
Here we are.

643
00:34:11.520 --> 00:34:13.520
Okay. so...

644
00:34:13.960 --> 00:34:15.000
Wait. where's our guy?

645
00:34:17.040 --> 00:34:18.040
And what is that?

646
00:34:19.640 --> 00:34:22.080
Oh. that? Don't worry about it.

647
00:34:22.400 --> 00:34:24.160
But I should probably warn you

648
00:34:24.680 --> 00:34:26.480
Delroy's owner is a chef.

649
00:34:27.120 --> 00:34:28.280
A... A chef?

650
00:34:28.480 --> 00:34:29.840
Yeah. A... A chef.

651
00:34:29.920 --> 00:34:32.280
Like a predator.
except instead of eating you

652
00:34:32.360 --> 00:34:34.880
he feeds you to a group
of much lazier predators.

653
00:34:35.800 --> 00:34:36.800
Right this way.

654
00:34:43.960 --> 00:34:45.240
After you.

655
00:34:56.720 --> 00:34:57.720
Hey.

656
00:35:03.320 --> 00:35:04.360
Coast is clear.

657
00:35:06.400 --> 00:35:09.800
Hey. Delroy. How's it going?
It's been a while.

658
00:35:09.880 --> 00:35:11.760
You look good. Slip me some feather.

659
00:35:11.840 --> 00:35:13.680
I brought you
a nice family of mallards.

660
00:35:13.760 --> 00:35:15.160
They need to ask you something.

661
00:35:19.640 --> 00:35:22.320
Well. Mr. Delroy

662
00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:24.520
so nice to meet you.

663
00:35:25.520 --> 00:35:27.560
Do you know the way to Jamaica?

664
00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:32.360
Do I know the way to Jamaica?

665
00:35:32.720 --> 00:35:34.880
Told ya.
He's a little sensitive about it.

666
00:35:34.960 --> 00:35:36.920
He was born and raised there.

667
00:35:37.280 --> 00:35:38.320
What happened?

668
00:35:38.520 --> 00:35:41.440
The chef snatched him up
in the middle of the night.

669
00:35:41.520 --> 00:35:44.360
Next day. old Del's gone
from free bird to jailbird.

670
00:35:45.360 --> 00:35:47.760
Come on. D.
Just tell them how to get there.

671
00:35:50.720 --> 00:35:52.040
Fly to the big green statue.

672
00:35:52.120 --> 00:35:53.240
Fly due south for three miles

673
00:35:53.320 --> 00:35:55.520
then due east for one mile.
due west for ten miles

674
00:35:55.600 --> 00:35:58.440
then you southwest for one mile.
south-southeast for two miles

675
00:35:58.520 --> 00:36:00.360
and south-southwest
for the rest of the way.

676
00:36:01.480 --> 00:36:04.120
And don't stop
until you see that mist

677
00:36:04.200 --> 00:36:07.880
dancing atop
the beautiful blue mountains.

678
00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:10.600
You can't miss it.

679
00:36:14.760 --> 00:36:16.840
Oh... no. No. don't cry. Big Red.

680
00:36:16.920 --> 00:36:18.880
It's all right.
We didn't mean to upset you.

681
00:36:18.960 --> 00:36:23.320
Jamaica!

682
00:36:24.040 --> 00:36:25.280
I miss my family.

683
00:36:25.360 --> 00:36:26.360
Devon.

684
00:36:26.720 --> 00:36:27.960
And likkle Donnie.

685
00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:30.280
Dolores. Deedee.

686
00:36:30.360 --> 00:36:32.920
Winston!

687
00:36:33.600 --> 00:36:34.800
That me cousin.

688
00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:38.520
Dad. we're not really gonna
leave him here. are we?

689
00:36:39.080 --> 00:36:41.200
He looks so cramped in that cage.

690
00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:42.960
Come on. blow it out.

691
00:36:43.400 --> 00:36:44.400
Blow.

692
00:36:47.600 --> 00:36:49.120
There's nothing we can do here. Dax.

693
00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:50.720
We could get the key.

694
00:36:50.800 --> 00:36:53.080
No. kid. That's impossible.

695
00:36:53.160 --> 00:36:54.760
Why? Where is it?

696
00:36:55.040 --> 00:36:56.200
Down there.

697
00:36:57.240 --> 00:36:59.800
The chef keeps that key
on him at all times.

698
00:36:59.880 --> 00:37:03.920
And trust me. you don't want to go
anywhere near that lunatic.

699
00:37:04.480 --> 00:37:08.360
Him catch ya. him turn you
into duck à l'orange.

700
00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:10.160
What's duck à l'orange?

701
00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:12.880
It's you with l'orange on top.

702
00:37:15.040 --> 00:37:16.800
You know what? Guys. don't worry.

703
00:37:16.880 --> 00:37:17.920
I'll go get it.

704
00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:19.080
What? No... no.

705
00:37:19.160 --> 00:37:20.760
Dad. it's okay. I've got this.

706
00:37:20.840 --> 00:37:22.240
No. you don't got this.

707
00:37:22.360 --> 00:37:24.920
But just because you're scared
of everything in the world

708
00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.440
doesn't mean I have to be.

709
00:37:29.280 --> 00:37:30.920
Okay. You know what?

710
00:37:31.200 --> 00:37:32.480
I will go get the key.

711
00:37:32.560 --> 00:37:33.960
Cool. I'm coming with you.

712
00:37:34.040 --> 00:37:35.240
No. You stay.

713
00:37:35.320 --> 00:37:36.320
Dad!

714
00:37:36.640 --> 00:37:38.320
Stay here.

715
00:38:27.520 --> 00:38:28.520
Wrong!

716
00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:18.520
How's it going?

717
00:39:19.640 --> 00:39:22.360
What are you doing here?
I told you to stay back there.

718
00:39:22.440 --> 00:39:24.800
Oh. there's no way
I'm letting you have all the fun.

719
00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:25.880
Let's go.

720
00:39:32.000 --> 00:39:33.000
There.

721
00:39:33.400 --> 00:39:34.400
Here.

722
00:39:34.920 --> 00:39:36.280
Grab my tail so I can get the key.

723
00:39:36.360 --> 00:39:37.360
Hurry.

724
00:39:50.280 --> 00:39:52.120
- Pam. Look.
- Almost there.

725
00:39:54.800 --> 00:39:56.320
- Pam.
- Almost there.

726
00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:00.720
- Pam.
- A little closer.

727
00:40:01.360 --> 00:40:02.360
Pam!

728
00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:04.760
Got it.

729
00:40:17.360 --> 00:40:18.520
Go... go!

730
00:40:28.000 --> 00:40:32.120
Duck à l'orange!

731
00:40:55.760 --> 00:40:58.560
<i>Keep on surviving</i>

732
00:41:03.560 --> 00:41:06.080
- What?
- Salsa Tuesdays.

733
00:41:14.200 --> 00:41:16.160
- We're doomed!
- Don't panic. Mack.

734
00:41:16.240 --> 00:41:18.120
I can't help it. It relaxes me.

735
00:41:18.200 --> 00:41:21.480
Mack. we're gonna make it. all right?
We have to be optimistic.

736
00:41:21.560 --> 00:41:24.160
Optimistic? How can we
be optimistic right now?

737
00:41:24.240 --> 00:41:26.720
Well. I don't know.
but if we are panicking

738
00:41:26.800 --> 00:41:30.120
we'll never find our way out!

739
00:41:32.480 --> 00:41:33.800
- That's it.
- What's it?

740
00:41:33.880 --> 00:41:35.040
Whatever you're doing

741
00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:36.360
keep doing it.

742
00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:39.200
You mean like this?

743
00:41:39.280 --> 00:41:40.760
Yes. Mack. It's working.

744
00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:50.200
Oh. we can do this. Mack.

745
00:41:54.720 --> 00:41:56.200
Okay. follow my lead.

746
00:42:35.240 --> 00:42:37.800
Dad. Mom. you were amazing.

747
00:42:37.880 --> 00:42:39.520
Thank you. Gwenny. but
we're in a bit of a hurry right now.

748
00:42:39.600 --> 00:42:40.800
- Pam. key.
- Here.

749
00:42:41.120 --> 00:42:42.480
Okay. Let's do this.

750
00:42:43.160 --> 00:42:44.160
'Urry! 'Urry!

751
00:42:44.240 --> 00:42:45.320
No. more to the right. To the right

752
00:42:45.400 --> 00:42:47.080
- and twist. Mack!
- No... no. My right. Dad.

753
00:42:47.160 --> 00:42:48.160
- Down. down.
- No. push.

754
00:42:48.240 --> 00:42:49.680
- To the right. Hold it and twist it.
- That's it! No. Dad.

755
00:42:49.760 --> 00:42:50.840
- Come on!
- Do I just have to do it?

756
00:42:50.920 --> 00:42:51.920
Push!

757
00:42:53.000 --> 00:42:54.040
Oh. What happened?

758
00:42:55.840 --> 00:42:58.200
Wait. where's the k...
Where's the key?

759
00:42:58.280 --> 00:43:00.160
- I swallowed it.
- Oh. that's a bummer.

760
00:43:00.240 --> 00:43:01.560
Spit it out. You need to spit it out!

761
00:43:01.640 --> 00:43:02.720
I'm on it. I'm on it.

762
00:43:04.480 --> 00:43:05.720
- Come on. Mack.
- Okay

763
00:43:05.800 --> 00:43:08.360
He's really close.
and he really looks mad.

764
00:43:11.920 --> 00:43:14.240
- Mack! Spit it out already.
- Oh. no... no!

765
00:43:16.920 --> 00:43:18.360
Come on! Hurry up!

766
00:43:23.400 --> 00:43:25.360
Come on. kids. Together.

767
00:43:25.440 --> 00:43:27.080
Spit it out!

768
00:43:27.560 --> 00:43:29.320
This isn't working!

769
00:43:30.560 --> 00:43:32.400
Bird eater incoming!

770
00:44:29.680 --> 00:44:30.680
Got it!

771
00:44:35.720 --> 00:44:38.920
I'm free!

772
00:44:43.480 --> 00:44:45.480
<i>Ya man!</i>

773
00:44:49.040 --> 00:44:50.520
We did it!

774
00:44:56.920 --> 00:44:59.120
Thank you!

775
00:45:02.120 --> 00:45:03.160
Oh. you did it.

776
00:45:03.240 --> 00:45:04.280
I can't believe it.

777
00:45:04.360 --> 00:45:06.240
I was in a cage. and now I'm not.

778
00:45:06.320 --> 00:45:07.800
In. and now not.

779
00:45:08.680 --> 00:45:10.920
And you did it! All of you.

780
00:45:11.320 --> 00:45:12.560
But you

781
00:45:12.960 --> 00:45:14.600
you wild duck. you!

782
00:45:14.840 --> 00:45:17.040
You must be the bravest duck
me ever meet.

783
00:45:17.120 --> 00:45:18.120
Oh. I'm not that...

784
00:45:19.320 --> 00:45:20.520
I'm not that brave.

785
00:45:20.600 --> 00:45:23.360
What? You knew the danger.
You did it anyway.

786
00:45:23.440 --> 00:45:24.680
What do you call that?

787
00:45:24.800 --> 00:45:27.760
Yeah. you're right. I guess
that is the only word that describes

788
00:45:28.320 --> 00:45:29.400
who I am.

789
00:45:29.480 --> 00:45:31.560
Did you hear that?
He called me brave.

790
00:45:31.880 --> 00:45:33.760
So you want to go to my island. eh?

791
00:45:33.840 --> 00:45:35.920
I will be honored
to take you there myself.

792
00:45:36.560 --> 00:45:37.640
You'd do that?

793
00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:40.040
For you. me do anything

794
00:45:40.120 --> 00:45:44.120
because I can do anything!

795
00:45:45.240 --> 00:45:47.760
I can go 'ere. or I could go 'ere.

796
00:45:48.280 --> 00:45:49.720
Free as a bird!

797
00:45:50.200 --> 00:45:51.240
Right.

798
00:45:51.320 --> 00:45:52.960
'Cause I'm a bird!

799
00:45:56.040 --> 00:45:58.400
I didn't think I'd ever say this. but

800
00:45:59.120 --> 00:46:01.200
you are one heck of a bird.

801
00:46:01.880 --> 00:46:04.000
Oh. Well. thanks. Chump.

802
00:46:04.400 --> 00:46:06.040
You're not so bad yourself.

803
00:46:08.080 --> 00:46:10.320
Yeah. you know. I'm getting
a little waterwork-y up here.

804
00:46:11.160 --> 00:46:13.520
Scram. you crazy ducks.
Get outta here.

805
00:46:13.760 --> 00:46:15.680
- Bye. Chump.
- Bye-bye. Chump.

806
00:46:15.760 --> 00:46:17.600
- Thank you!
- Thanks for everything.

807
00:46:17.680 --> 00:46:18.800
So long. Chump.

808
00:46:19.480 --> 00:46:21.680
Don't forget
where you got that sandwich.

809
00:46:25.240 --> 00:46:27.400
Bye-bye. you country bumpkins.

810
00:46:27.480 --> 00:46:28.680
I love you!

811
00:46:49.160 --> 00:46:50.760
I can't believe it!

812
00:46:50.840 --> 00:46:52.720
In a few hours.
we'll reach the coast.

813
00:46:52.800 --> 00:46:57.200
Then a little hop over the ocean.
and we'll finally get to my homeland!

814
00:46:57.440 --> 00:46:58.440
Hey. Delroy

815
00:46:58.800 --> 00:47:02.720
is it true that
the sea glows at night in Jamaica?

816
00:47:02.800 --> 00:47:06.000
Because that sounds
incredibly magical.

817
00:47:07.600 --> 00:47:09.240
You 'ear about that. eh?

818
00:47:09.320 --> 00:47:11.320
Whatever you're expecting over there

819
00:47:12.200 --> 00:47:14.680
it's going to be even better.

820
00:47:16.280 --> 00:47:20.080
Jamaica. I'm coming home!

821
00:47:20.160 --> 00:47:22.120
- <i>I'm coming. I'm coming</i>
- Mom?

822
00:47:22.200 --> 00:47:24.200
<i>I'm coming home</i>

823
00:47:24.280 --> 00:47:26.960
I really need to wee-wee.
It's really bad.

824
00:47:27.040 --> 00:47:29.600
It's okay. Gwen.
You can do it while we fly.

825
00:47:29.680 --> 00:47:32.000
Here? But anyone could see me.

826
00:47:32.080 --> 00:47:34.760
No one's watching. Gwen.
You know what? I'll go up front.

827
00:47:35.600 --> 00:47:36.600
What's happening?

828
00:47:37.120 --> 00:47:38.600
We have a number two situation.

829
00:47:38.680 --> 00:47:39.680
Oh.

830
00:47:39.760 --> 00:47:41.320
- Everything okay back there?
- Dad!

831
00:47:41.400 --> 00:47:42.600
- Oops! Sorry. Gwen!
- Don't look! What are you doing?

832
00:47:42.680 --> 00:47:43.680
My bad! My bad!

833
00:47:44.680 --> 00:47:46.720
Mom. I can't do it here.

834
00:47:46.800 --> 00:47:47.800
Can we land?

835
00:47:47.920 --> 00:47:50.840
No. we won't land. Gwen. You're old
enough to do it in the sky now.

836
00:47:50.920 --> 00:47:53.680
But it's too much pressure.
and it's gross.

837
00:47:53.760 --> 00:47:55.760
It's not gross. We're birds.

838
00:47:55.840 --> 00:47:57.360
Every bird does it in the sky.

839
00:47:57.440 --> 00:47:59.160
What if someone is looking
down there?

840
00:47:59.240 --> 00:48:00.920
No one is looking down there.

841
00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:04.040
I told you. we are not landing.
There is no way we're landing.

842
00:48:06.000 --> 00:48:07.640
Are you sure no one's watching?

843
00:48:07.720 --> 00:48:10.200
Gwen Mallard!
Do it now or we leave without you.

844
00:48:10.280 --> 00:48:11.480
Okay. okay.

845
00:48:11.720 --> 00:48:12.840
She's perfectly capable

846
00:48:12.920 --> 00:48:14.000
- of doing her business in the sky
- It's okay. Pam.

847
00:48:14.080 --> 00:48:15.720
- and yet here we are.
- Just let her be.

848
00:48:15.800 --> 00:48:17.640
Does anybody have a soft moss?

849
00:48:17.720 --> 00:48:19.040
Just use a leaf!

850
00:48:20.840 --> 00:48:22.600
Someone's watching!
Someone's watching!

851
00:48:22.680 --> 00:48:24.360
- There! Someone's watching!
- Where? Where?

852
00:48:39.240 --> 00:48:42.200
Follow me. and stay close.

853
00:48:42.800 --> 00:48:43.800
For real. Dad?

854
00:48:45.920 --> 00:48:46.920
Cool.

855
00:48:47.000 --> 00:48:48.440
I like your spirit. duck man.

856
00:48:51.080 --> 00:48:52.080
Guys?

857
00:48:55.560 --> 00:48:57.280
Are you sure this is safe?

858
00:48:57.360 --> 00:49:00.720
Don't worry. That wild duck
is on a journey of the soul

859
00:49:00.800 --> 00:49:02.440
and I say we follow him.

860
00:49:02.760 --> 00:49:05.040
But just in case.
get out your talons.

861
00:49:06.040 --> 00:49:08.520
I ain't sure
ducks have talons. though.

862
00:49:19.720 --> 00:49:22.280
Now stretch your back

863
00:49:22.360 --> 00:49:26.320
and move your wings up to the sky.

864
00:49:26.680 --> 00:49:28.440
Breathe in.

865
00:49:28.680 --> 00:49:34.000
And breathe out.

866
00:49:34.080 --> 00:49:36.200
Excellent. class.

867
00:49:36.280 --> 00:49:39.480
And now the egg position.

868
00:49:42.640 --> 00:49:44.320
And we hatch

869
00:49:44.400 --> 00:49:48.000
with a newborn quack.

870
00:49:48.520 --> 00:49:50.400
Quack.

871
00:49:50.760 --> 00:49:53.320
Very good. And repeat.

872
00:49:53.800 --> 00:49:55.200
Quack.

873
00:49:55.280 --> 00:49:56.680
And repeat.

874
00:49:56.760 --> 00:49:57.960
Quack.

875
00:49:58.040 --> 00:49:59.840
And repeat.

876
00:50:00.080 --> 00:50:01.680
Hey. what's going on here?

877
00:50:02.760 --> 00:50:04.000
Visitors!

878
00:50:06.040 --> 00:50:07.400
Brothers. brothers.

879
00:50:07.480 --> 00:50:09.240
Sisters. hold your enthusiasm.

880
00:50:09.320 --> 00:50:11.880
We don't want to scare
our guests away. do we?

881
00:50:12.440 --> 00:50:13.760
Hello. friends.

882
00:50:13.840 --> 00:50:15.320
I am Googoo.

883
00:50:15.400 --> 00:50:17.880
Welcome to our humble abode.

884
00:50:17.960 --> 00:50:20.720
Abode? What is going on here?

885
00:50:20.800 --> 00:50:22.880
Our morning relaxation

886
00:50:22.960 --> 00:50:26.360
as we prepare
for the glorious Earl and Mae

887
00:50:26.440 --> 00:50:29.960
to open the gates to paradise.

888
00:50:30.040 --> 00:50:33.520
Oh. you're so lucky.
You're just in time.

889
00:50:45.840 --> 00:50:47.200
My friends...

890
00:50:47.560 --> 00:50:52.120
welcome to the Garden of Harmony.

891
00:50:59.920 --> 00:51:01.680
I don't understand. It's...

892
00:51:01.760 --> 00:51:03.320
Heaven for ducks?

893
00:51:03.920 --> 00:51:05.480
Yep. pretty much.

894
00:51:21.520 --> 00:51:22.520
Perfect.

895
00:51:38.960 --> 00:51:42.320
You came to the perfect place.
my friends.

896
00:51:42.840 --> 00:51:46.920
Here. humans spare no expense
on our well-being.

897
00:51:47.000 --> 00:51:49.640
And they just finished
building our brand-new slide.

898
00:51:49.960 --> 00:51:51.200
Yeah!

899
00:51:51.640 --> 00:51:53.640
So please. be our guest.

900
00:51:53.720 --> 00:51:57.320
Feel free to enjoy our place
for as long as you like.

901
00:51:59.720 --> 00:52:02.800
Well. I guess we could
take the afternoon.

902
00:52:04.760 --> 00:52:06.080
- Come on. Please.
- Come on. Dad. please.

903
00:52:06.160 --> 00:52:07.760
- Come on. Let's stay. Stay.
- Please.

904
00:52:07.840 --> 00:52:09.240
- Please.
- Oh. no... no.

905
00:52:09.320 --> 00:52:11.080
I don't think
we can possibly stay here...

906
00:52:12.200 --> 00:52:15.600
without having
the best time of our lives!

907
00:52:15.680 --> 00:52:17.640
Now. get out there and have some fun.

908
00:52:17.720 --> 00:52:18.720
Yay!

909
00:52:18.800 --> 00:52:20.800
- Slides. here I come!
- Wait for me!

910
00:52:20.880 --> 00:52:22.200
Slippy slides!

911
00:52:35.120 --> 00:52:38.400
Here comes the sea dragon!

912
00:52:43.360 --> 00:52:45.000
- We're gonna get you!
- We're gonna squish

913
00:52:45.080 --> 00:52:46.680
your sea dragon face!

914
00:52:46.760 --> 00:52:48.760
Sea dragon is hungry.

915
00:52:52.760 --> 00:52:54.880
We need to slay the sea dragon!

916
00:52:56.480 --> 00:52:58.920
- Gwen.
- Gwen. be more careful.

917
00:52:59.000 --> 00:53:00.760
We need to slay him gently.

918
00:53:01.360 --> 00:53:02.600
Really? Okay.

919
00:53:05.760 --> 00:53:06.760
Uncle Dan.

920
00:53:06.840 --> 00:53:08.360
What? I want to play. too.

921
00:53:08.760 --> 00:53:10.360
Sea dragon needs a break.

922
00:53:11.800 --> 00:53:12.800
Gwen!

923
00:53:32.600 --> 00:53:35.440
Brothers. sisters. great news!

924
00:53:35.520 --> 00:53:38.400
Earl and Mae are taking us
on a field trip.

925
00:53:38.480 --> 00:53:39.800
I'm so excited.

926
00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:41.880
It's so great. Hurry. guys.

927
00:53:41.960 --> 00:53:43.160
Hurry. It's time.

928
00:53:43.240 --> 00:53:44.400
You don't want to miss this.

929
00:53:44.480 --> 00:53:46.160
Come on. everyone. Let's go.

930
00:53:50.560 --> 00:53:52.600
No... no!

931
00:53:52.680 --> 00:53:53.960
I'm so excited. I can't wait

932
00:53:54.040 --> 00:53:55.960
- to get started.
- Googoo. stop!

933
00:53:56.200 --> 00:53:57.480
What is it. my little friend?

934
00:53:57.840 --> 00:53:59.280
The chef. The...

935
00:54:00.960 --> 00:54:02.040
You want to come. too?

936
00:54:02.120 --> 00:54:03.280
Come on. Let's go.

937
00:54:03.360 --> 00:54:05.600
- You got to stop. Googoo!
- Last one is a rotten egg.

938
00:54:05.680 --> 00:54:07.000
- Stop! Googoo!
- Kneel!

939
00:54:07.080 --> 00:54:08.440
Sea dragon. kneel!

940
00:54:08.520 --> 00:54:09.720
- Googoo. no!
- Gwenny.

941
00:54:09.800 --> 00:54:11.000
- Stop!
- No. Don't hit your father.

942
00:54:11.120 --> 00:54:12.560
- What?
- Googoo!

943
00:54:12.640 --> 00:54:13.880
- Where are you going?
- Googoo!

944
00:54:14.320 --> 00:54:15.880
Delroy is the sea dragon now.

945
00:54:15.960 --> 00:54:17.880
Of course. I'd love that.

946
00:54:17.960 --> 00:54:19.240
- You're next!
- No. no. no.

947
00:54:19.320 --> 00:54:20.720
You're gonna be gentle. Okay?

948
00:54:21.160 --> 00:54:23.600
Gwenny. come on! He said "gently."

949
00:54:23.680 --> 00:54:24.840
Googoo. he's gonna take you

950
00:54:24.920 --> 00:54:25.920
- to his kitchen. He's gonna
- Come on.

951
00:54:26.000 --> 00:54:27.640
serve you to people. with oranges.

952
00:54:27.720 --> 00:54:29.240
Hey. hey. What's happening?

953
00:54:29.560 --> 00:54:31.720
Dad. it's the chef. He's back.

954
00:54:36.640 --> 00:54:40.040
Earl and Mae are giving those ducks
to the chef so he can cook them!

955
00:54:40.120 --> 00:54:41.440
I beg your pardon?

956
00:54:41.520 --> 00:54:43.800
Dax. go back to Mom.
I'll handle this.

957
00:54:43.880 --> 00:54:45.280
No! I can help!

958
00:54:45.360 --> 00:54:47.000
- I can just...
- Go back to Mom now!

959
00:54:47.080 --> 00:54:48.680
Googoo. do not get on that truck.

960
00:54:48.760 --> 00:54:52.080
Look. I understand this is all new
to you. Bit weird. bit strange.

961
00:54:52.160 --> 00:54:54.360
Don't you get it? It's a trap!
We've gotta get your ducks

962
00:54:54.440 --> 00:54:55.800
- out of here!
- Everyone. get off the truck

963
00:54:55.880 --> 00:54:57.120
unless you want to be cooked!

964
00:54:57.720 --> 00:54:59.280
- Cooked?
- Wait. what's that?

965
00:54:59.360 --> 00:55:02.640
Come on! Hurry!
You gotta go before he comes back.

966
00:55:11.040 --> 00:55:12.040
Let go!

967
00:55:12.240 --> 00:55:14.080
- Earl and Mae are our leaders.
- Dax?

968
00:55:14.160 --> 00:55:15.520
- They massage us.
- Dax!

969
00:55:32.280 --> 00:55:34.800
Everyone. run! Now!

970
00:55:40.840 --> 00:55:42.960
- Pam. the chef!
- What?

971
00:55:43.200 --> 00:55:44.680
We have to get out of here now!

972
00:55:44.760 --> 00:55:45.920
Go. go. go!

973
00:55:48.280 --> 00:55:51.440
Okay. let's go... let's go! Go... go!

974
00:55:51.600 --> 00:55:52.800
Everyone. take off!

975
00:55:55.480 --> 00:55:56.800
Dax. on my back!

976
00:55:59.120 --> 00:56:00.120
Hurry!

977
00:56:23.280 --> 00:56:26.360
Guys. we need to rest. Follow me.

978
00:56:37.520 --> 00:56:39.720
Guys. are you okay? What happened?

979
00:56:39.800 --> 00:56:41.600
- Mom. he was coming for the...
- I'll tell you what happened.

980
00:56:41.680 --> 00:56:44.440
I told him to stay back.
and he almost got himself killed.

981
00:56:45.000 --> 00:56:46.840
But. Dad. I was trying to help.

982
00:56:46.920 --> 00:56:48.400
I don't need your help. Dax.

983
00:56:48.480 --> 00:56:50.000
I need you to do what I say!

984
00:56:50.080 --> 00:56:51.840
Do you understand?

985
00:56:59.800 --> 00:57:00.960
Listen. Dax.

986
00:57:01.040 --> 00:57:03.200
Just let us grown-ups
figure it out while...

987
00:57:09.080 --> 00:57:10.760
All right. everyone.
let's call it a night.

988
00:57:11.680 --> 00:57:13.040
We could use the rest.

989
00:58:22.560 --> 00:58:24.480
Gwen. you scared me.

990
00:58:24.560 --> 00:58:25.680
You look mad.

991
00:58:26.280 --> 00:58:27.760
You need a hug!

992
00:58:28.880 --> 00:58:30.920
No. Gwen. I don't need a hug.

993
00:58:32.080 --> 00:58:33.960
- I said no hug.
- Don't fight it.

994
00:58:34.040 --> 00:58:35.560
It'll make you feel better.

995
00:58:39.160 --> 00:58:40.200
Can you let go now?

996
00:58:40.280 --> 00:58:41.960
- You feel better?
- No.

997
00:58:42.040 --> 00:58:43.640
Then it hasn't kicked in yet.

998
00:58:47.760 --> 00:58:49.440
- What about now?
- No.

999
00:58:49.640 --> 00:58:50.640
Now?

1000
00:58:51.120 --> 00:58:52.400
- Now?
- Nothing.

1001
00:58:52.480 --> 00:58:53.840
- A little?
- Nope.

1002
00:58:53.920 --> 00:58:55.000
I felt something.

1003
00:59:09.320 --> 00:59:10.320
No!

1004
00:59:15.200 --> 00:59:16.800
Oh. no. he's back!

1005
00:59:16.880 --> 00:59:18.320
Every duck for himself!

1006
00:59:18.400 --> 00:59:20.000
- Kids!
- Dax! Gwen!

1007
00:59:26.920 --> 00:59:28.600
- Mom! Dad!
- No. no. no!

1008
00:59:28.680 --> 00:59:30.880
- No. no! Dax. Gwen. stay back!
- No! Stop!

1009
00:59:31.760 --> 00:59:33.400
- Get out of here now!
- Go hide!

1010
00:59:33.480 --> 00:59:34.960
- Hide. kids! Go!
- Go. go!

1011
00:59:50.760 --> 00:59:51.760
No!

1012
00:59:54.360 --> 00:59:55.680
- No. no. no.
- No!

1013
00:59:55.760 --> 00:59:57.640
- Mom. Dad. no!
- Daddy!

1014
00:59:57.720 --> 00:59:59.480
Oh. kids! Oh. kids!

1015
00:59:59.560 --> 01:00:00.560
No!

1016
01:00:00.640 --> 01:00:01.760
No!

1017
01:01:01.960 --> 01:01:04.520
He's gonna cook
Mom and Dad. isn't he?

1018
01:01:04.600 --> 01:01:06.480
And he's gonna come back for us.

1019
01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:08.680
And he'll cook us. too!

1020
01:01:09.040 --> 01:01:12.520
I wish we tasted awful!

1021
01:01:13.520 --> 01:01:17.520
Gwen. we're not giving up. okay?
We're gonna figure something out.

1022
01:01:19.360 --> 01:01:20.600
- We are?
- Yes.

1023
01:01:20.680 --> 01:01:21.880
There has to be a way.

1024
01:01:21.960 --> 01:01:23.560
But... but how?

1025
01:01:23.640 --> 01:01:25.120
You can't even fly.

1026
01:01:25.440 --> 01:01:26.680
Oh. we're doomed.

1027
01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:42.800
Gwen. you're a genius.

1028
01:01:44.320 --> 01:01:45.320
Am I?

1029
01:01:50.840 --> 01:01:54.000
We are not getting cooked today!

1030
01:01:57.360 --> 01:01:58.800
Come on. Pam. keep going.

1031
01:02:03.080 --> 01:02:04.160
Pam?

1032
01:02:04.240 --> 01:02:05.320
It's hopeless. Mack.

1033
01:02:05.760 --> 01:02:09.000
What? No... no. it's not hopeless.
We can do this.

1034
01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:10.200
We've lost them.

1035
01:02:10.760 --> 01:02:12.960
Mack. we've lost the kids.
You were right.

1036
01:02:13.040 --> 01:02:15.000
We never ever should
have left the pond.

1037
01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:17.640
Pam. enough. This isn't you.

1038
01:02:17.720 --> 01:02:20.880
You're the adventurous one.
the brave one.

1039
01:02:20.960 --> 01:02:22.600
You never give up on anything.

1040
01:02:23.360 --> 01:02:25.560
You... you haven't
even given up on me.

1041
01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:27.680
Come on. Pam.

1042
01:02:27.960 --> 01:02:29.480
You've proven over and over again

1043
01:02:29.560 --> 01:02:31.920
that when everything is hopeless.
we have to be...

1044
01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:33.680
Optimistic.

1045
01:02:33.760 --> 01:02:37.920
Yes. And now you and me
are going to get our kids back

1046
01:02:38.000 --> 01:02:41.080
so we can finish
this crazy. wonderful adventure.

1047
01:02:41.160 --> 01:02:43.640
And we are going to show them
that when danger strikes

1048
01:02:43.720 --> 01:02:45.360
you do not run from it.

1049
01:02:45.440 --> 01:02:47.520
You take a stand!

1050
01:02:49.480 --> 01:02:51.280
That's it! Look. Pam...

1051
01:02:54.600 --> 01:02:55.760
We can do this.

1052
01:02:55.840 --> 01:02:58.280
